&lt;p&gt;Welcome to VoteYour a place to speak up, share your thoughts, and explore what others think, all without revealing your identity. These Terms and Conditions explain your rights and responsibilities when using our platform.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use of VoteYour constitutes your acknowledgment and acceptance of our terms of service.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Your use of Vote Your&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;VoteYour is built for open, respectful expression. You can:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Participate in or create polls on topics that matter to you.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Vote anonymously and view results in real time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Share ideas without revealing personal information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You may not:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Post an offensive or discriminatory comment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Interfere with the site&rsquo;s functionality or other users&rsquo; experience.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Attempt to exploit, reverse engineer, or misuse the platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We reserve the right to remove content or block accounts that violate these principles.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Account Access&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can browse polls without signing up. If you choose to register, we ask only for your email address to help you log in securely.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Keep your login credentials private. You are responsible for any activity done under your account.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Content ownership and responsibility&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You own the content you create (polls, comments, etc.), but you give VoteYour the right to display and store that content on our platform.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You are responsible for what you post. Don&rsquo;t upload anything you don&rsquo;t have the right to, and don&rsquo;t impersonate others.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Privacy and Data Use&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We care about privacy. Seriously.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We collect minimal data&mdash;mainly your email (if you sign up), voting activity (stored anonymously), and basic technical information.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We don&rsquo;t sell your data, track your identity, or use third-party ads.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Read our Privacy Policy for the full breakdown.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Cookies and Technology&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We use cookies only for functionality, such as keeping you logged in and remembering your preferences. We don&rsquo;t use them for advertising or creepy tracking.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can manage cookies through your browser at any time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Availability of Platform&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We do our best to keep VoteYour running 24/7, but we can&rsquo;t guarantee there will be no interruptions or bugs. If maintenance or outages occur, we will aim to notify users as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Changes to the Platform or Terms&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We may update these Terms occasionally. Major changes will be announced on the website or via email. Continuing to use the site means you accept any updated terms.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Termination&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can suspend or deactivate your account if you break these terms, especially if your behavior harms the community or the integrity of the platform.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can delete your account anytime from your settings or by contacting us. When you do, we erase your personal data from our system.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Liability Disclaimer&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;VoteYour provides this service &ldquo;as is.&rdquo; We are&nbsp; not responsible for:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The accuracy or legality of user-generated content&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Any consequences of the poll results or discussions&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Downtime, data loss, or technical glitches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use the platform responsibly and at your own discretion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Governing Law&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These Terms are governed by the applicable laws of the jurisdiction in which the agreement is executed. Any legal disputes arising will be resolved in the courts of that jurisdiction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Have questions?&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&rsquo;re here to help. For questions or concerns about these terms, reach out to us!&lt;/p&gt;
